---
description: Prevent direct commits on protected branches
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Branch Safety

- Before any `git commit`, `git push`, or PR creation, run:
  - `git branch --show-current`
  - `git status --short -b`
- If branch is `develop`, `main`, or `master`, stop and ask:
  `Create/switch to a feature branch before committing?`
- Never commit directly to `develop`, `main`, or `master` unless the user explicitly says:
  `commit directly to <branch>`.
- Prefer branch names based on an issue key when available (example: `pcserve-450-short-description`).
- After a commit, report the exact branch used and whether protected local branches were modified.
